        <!-- Historical Importance -->
        <section>
            <h2>Historical Importance</h2>
            <p>  Historically, Peruvanthanam was a crucial stopover for traders traveling between the high ranges and the lowlands, fostering a blend of cultures and traditions.The region holds religious significance due to the presence of churches and temples that date back centuries. Traditional festivals celebrated here reflect the town's enduring connection to its roots.</p>
        </section>

        <!-- Educational Institutions -->
        <section>
            <h2>Educational Institutions</h2>
            <p>Peruvanthanam takes pride in its educational institutions, providing opportunities for young minds to thrive. Key institutions include:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><b>St Joseph's Higher Secondary School Chuzhup</b>: A school known for its academic excellence and holistic development of students.</li>
                <li><b>Government UP School</b>: A reputed institution focused on modern education methods and extracurricular activities.</li>
                <li><b>St. Antony's College</b>: A hub for higher education, inspiring students to achieve academic and personal success.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- Healthcare Facilities -->
        <section>
            <h2>Healthcare Facilities</h2>
            <p>Peruvanthanam ensures the well-being of its residents with accessible healthcare facilities, including:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><b>Peruvanthanam Public Health Centre</b>: Offering essential health services to the local community.</li>
                <li><b>Private Clinics</b>: Providing specialized treatments with experienced medical professionals.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- Recreational Spots -->
        <section>
            <h2>Recreational Spots</h2>
            <p>Recreational activities and tourist destinations in and around Peruvanthanam make it a delightful place to explore:</p>
            <ul>

                <li><b>Mountain Bike Kerala</b>: Offers equipment hire and bike tours.</li>
                <li><b>Panchalimedu</b>: A popular point of interest and landmark.</li>
                <li><b>Sita Devi Lake</b>: A serene body of water.</li>
                <li><b>Barren Hills</b>: Offers scenic views.</li>
                <li><b>Vagamon Orchidarium and Floriculture Project</b>: A nature and wildlife area.</li>
                <li><b>Vagamon Pine Forest</b>: A picturesque landmark.</li>
                <li><b>Valanjamkanam Water Falls</b>: A beautiful waterfall.</li>
                <li><b>Parunthumpara</b>: A scenic walking area with lookouts.</li>
                <li><b>Pattumalay Tea Factory</b>: A place to explore tea plantations.</li>
                <li><b>Vagamon Lake</b>: Another serene body of water.</li>
            </ul>
